mnoGoSearch v.3.3  by mnoGoSearch Developers Team
Full featured web search engine
Please see the file COPYING for license information
===================================================


General
-------

mnoGoSearch is a full-featured SQL based web search engine.
mnoGoSearch consists of two parts. The first part is indexing mechanism (indexer).
Indexer walks over html hypertext references and stores found words and
new references into an SQL database. The second part is web CGI front-end to
provide search using data collected by indexer.
There are also PHP3 and Perl front-ends available from our site
http://www.mnogosearch.org/.


Main features are:
* SQLite, MySQL, PostgreSQL, IBM DB2, InterBase, Oracle, 
  MS SQL, Mimer, Sybase backends support.
* iODBC, unixODBC, EasySoft ODBC-ODBC bridge interfaces support.
* HTTP support
* HTTP proxy support
* HTTPS support
* FTP support
* NNTP support (both news:// and nntp:// URL schemes)
* HTDB virtual URL scheme support
  You can build a full-text index on big text columns
  of your SQL table.
* text/html, text/plain and text/xml built-in support
* external parsers support for other document types
* gzip, compress, deflate Content-Encoding support
* it can search for all of the word forms using 
  ispell affixes and dictionaries
* synonyms support
* basic authorization support. One may index password protected
  intranet HTTP servers
* proxy authorization support
* it's reenterant. One may use several indexing and searching processes 
  at the same time even on the same database.
* Multi-threaded indexing support
* stop-list support
* <META NAME="robots" content="..."> and robots.txt support
* C language CGI, PHP3, Perl web front-ends
* phrase search
* boolean query language support
* best documents are found first
* almost all widely used character sets support, including multi-byte
  Korean, Chinese, Japanese character sets as well as UTF8.
* automatic language/charset guesser for about 70 language/charset
  combinations
* HTML templates to easily customize search results
* advanced search options like time limits etc.


Where to get it?
----------------

Check for the latest version of mnoGoSearch at:
http://www.mnogosearch.org/


Support
-------

You can get help with mnoGoSearch using our mail lists
and webboards. We also offer some extended support options.
Please refer to our support page for further information:

http://www.mnogosearch.org/support.html


How do I use it?
----------------

Please read INSTALL for installation instructions and 
files in /doc subdirectory to start using mnoGoSearch.
Online documentation is available at 
  http://www.mnogosearch.org/doc.html

Contribution
------------

If you want to contribute to the development, have
some ideas or patches, please write to the mnoGoSearch
Developers Team <devel@mnogosearch.org>.


